HIGH PRIORITY — fixes the dominant latency/hang issue.

Octopus's HTTP client has no Timeout/IdleConnTimeout/etc. set.
A stalled upstream hangs the entire request indefinitely; failover
never kicks in for non-streaming calls because the iterator can't
advance until the previous attempt errors.

Adds:
  - per-request Timeout (configurable, default 90s)
  - Dial/TLS handshake timeouts
  - ResponseHeaderTimeout for fast-fail on stuck origins
  - MaxIdleConns / IdleConnTimeout for connection reuse hygiene

After applying this, Octopus will fall through to the next channel
within ~60-90 seconds of a hang instead of indefinitely.
